<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
  </head>
  
  <body>
    <div id="header">
      <nav class="uk-navbar">
<!--         <div class="uk-container uk-container-center"> -->
        <div class="uk-navbar-flip" style="padding:5px; padding-right:1em">

        <%= form_for("user", html: {class: 'uk-form'}, url: user_session_path) do |f| %>
        <%= f.text_field :email, placeholder: "Email" %>
        <%= f.password_field :password, placeholder: "Password" %>
        <%= f.submit 'Sign in', class: "uk-button" %>
<!--         </div> -->
        </div>
      </nav>
    </div>

    <div class="uk-grid" style="height:100%; max-height:60em">
      <div class='landing_panel uk-width-1-1'>
        <br><br>

        <div class='signin_options'>
          <%= f.check_box :remember_me %>
          <%= f.label :remember_me %>
          <% end %>
          <br>
          <%= link_to "Forgot your password?", new_password_path('user') %>
        </div>

        <div class="welcome">
          <h2 style= 'font-size: 200%; color:#333;'>Welcome to</h2>
          <h1 style= 'color:#0077dd; font-size: 450%; margin-top:0 !important;'>DeepThought</h1>
          <p style= 'color:#333;'>A tool to organize your mind.</p>
          <br>
          <div style='background-color:#444; color:lightGray; border:none; display: inline-block; text-align: left; float:center' class='uk-panel-box sign-up'>          
            <%= form_for(resource, :as => resource_name, :url => registration_path(resource_name), :html => {class: 'uk-form'}) do |f| %>

              <%= devise_error_messages! %>
              

              <div><%= f.label :email %><br />
              <%= f.email_field :email %></div>

              <div><%= f.label :password %><br />
              <%= f.password_field :password %></div>

              <div><%= f.label :password_confirmation %><br />
              <%= f.password_field :password_confirmation %></div>

              <div style='text-align: center; color:#444'><%= f.submit "Sign up", class: "uk-button uk-button-primary uk-button-large", style:"background-color:#0077dd; color:white; margin-top:0.75em" %><br>
             
            <% end %> 
              
            <%= form_for("user", html: {class: 'uk-form'}, url: user_session_path) do |f| %>
              <%= f.hidden_field :email, value: "i@ire.ne" %>
              <%= f.hidden_field :password, value: "soInsecure1" %>
              <%= f.submit 'Sign in as Demo User', class: "uk-button-link", style:"color:#ddd; margin-top:0.5em"%>
              </div>
            <% end %>
          </div>
        </div>
<!-- 
        <br><br><br><br><br> -->
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="panel_container uk-grid uk-grid-divider">
      <div class="uk-width-small-1-2">
        <div class="uk-panel">
          <h2><a href="#about" data-uk-smooth-scroll >About</a></h2>
            <div id="about">
            <p>Collect all of your thoughts on a single uncluttered page. Whether you're creating a simple to-do list, brainstorming for a paper, or outlining plans, DeepThought will help you break down your workload into small manageable bits.
            </p>
            <p>It's simple. Start with a list of items, say your projects. In each project, let's make a list of all the steps, and in each step, a list of substeps, and so on. DeepThought helps you focus on the task at hand. It lets you drill down through each level: showing only the relevant bits until you're ready to zoom back out. Keyboard shortcuts let you quickly navigate through each level and reorganize as needed.
            </p>
            <p>DeepThought is better experienced than explained. Try out a <a>demo </a> here or <a>create your account</a> today.
            </p><br>
            <p>Inspired by <a href="http//www.workflowy.com">Workflowy</a></p>
            </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="uk-width-small-1-2">
        <div class="uk-panel">
          <h2><a href="#technical" data-uk-smooth-scroll>Technical Aspects</a></h2>
            <div id="technical">
              <p>DeepThought uses Ruby on Rails and Backbone. Views are generated with Marionette.</p>
              <p>The view is generated by recursively calling Marionette compositeView: for each bullet, we generate a model view of a textbox, followed by a collection view of its children. The order of bullet points are preserved by storing rank amongst sibling bullet points, and storing parent/children relationships. Data is updated upon change on the client side as well as the server side, to ensure that the order is maintained upon navigation.</p>
            </div>
          <h2><a href="#incoming" data-uk-smooth-scroll>Incoming Features</a></h2>
            <div id="incoming">
              DeepThought is still under development. Here are a list of features to be added:
                <ul style='list-style :●'>
                  <li>Drag and drop</li>
                  <li>Sharing and collaboration</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </body>

</html>

<script>
$(document).ready(function(){
  window.DeepThought.initialize();
}); 

</script>